text.tspan: To account for varying topography and water in each
region, the "urban population" is the total number of
people living only in areas with a population density
Rail transit on these maps includes regional rail,
commuter rail, metro, and light rail transit (LRT).
Urban residents are "near rail transit" if they are
within 1km of a rail transit station on these routes
